-- GM, Chrysler willing to merge if a condition for aid: CEOs
-- 
-- Thu Dec 4, 2008 3:29pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/12/04/us-gm-chrysler-sb-idUSTRE4B375K20081204

 

 (Reuters) - Chrysler CEO Nardelli said on Thursday at a Senate Banking Committee hearing that his company is ready to accept a GM merger if that is a condition of receiving government funding. 

 Other highlights: * US Sen. Robert Bennett says a GM, chrysler merger is "a marriage that makes sense" and could be completed quickly * GM CEO Rick Wagoner says analysis of GM, Chrysler merger "showed significant cost savings" and he is willing to consider a merger if a condition of federal funding * Chrysler CEO Robert Nardelli says believes merger with GM would have produced savings of between $8 billion to $10 billion, and that his job would be the first to be cut * Chrysler CEO says challenge now is looking how to get synergies between two or among all three of the big three U.S. automakers * UAW's Ron Gettelfinger says experts disagree on cost-saving from merger and that job loss would be "unbelievable" * UAW's Gettelfinger says Chrysler needs alliances, not merger * GM CEO Wagoner says would prefer to work with UAW to consider Chrysler merger